In 1869, under the new {{ill|Kazoku|ja|華族}} system, the Takakura family was ennobled as part of the {{ill|Kazoku|ja|華族}} hierarchy. In 1884, {{ill|Takakura Naganori|ja|高倉永則}}, a former military officer, was granted the title of {{ill|Viscount|ja|子爵}} {{sfn|Odabe Yuji|2006|p=332}}.

== Notable Members ==
- {{ill|Takakura Nagasue|ja|高倉永季}}
- {{ill|Takakura Nagayoshi|ja|高倉永祜}}
- {{ill|Takakura Naganori|ja|高倉永則}}

== Related Institutions ==

The family archives, including historical documents, texts, and ceremonial garments, are preserved by the Yūsoku Cultural Institute (formerly the Takakura Cultural Institute). This organization is committed to preserving the traditions associated with the Takakura lineage.

