Their branch family, the {{ill|Horikawa Family|ja|堀河家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Horikawa Family|qq=}}, also belonged to the {{ill|Feather-Forest House|ja|羽林家|1=Baronial Houses|1=Baronial Houses|2=ja|3=羽林家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Feather-Forest House|qq=}} and held the [[:en:Viscount|Viscount]] title {{sfn|Kazoku Daikan Kanko Kai|1990|p=413}}.

== History ==

The family originated with [[:en:Fujiwara no Nagara|Fujiwara Nagano]], a son of [[:en:Fujiwara no Fuyutsugu|Fujiwara no Fuyutsugu]], and developed through his sixth son {{ill|Fujiwara Kiyotsune|ja|藤原清経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Kiyotsune|qq=}} {{Sfn|Kazoku Daikan Kanko Kai|1990|p=164}}. Over the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]] and [[:en:Kamakura period|Kamakura period]], few family members achieved {{ill|Kugyō|ja|Kugyō|1=Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kugyō|13=User:Immanuelle/Kugyō|qq=}} Rank<ref name="kotobank">{{Cite Kotobank|word=高倉家|encyclopedia=世界大百科事典 第２版、日本大百科全書(ニッポニカ)|accessdate=2022-11-16}}</ref>. In the [[:en:Northern and Southern Courts period (disambiguation)|Nanboku-chō period]], {{ill|Takakura Nagasue|ja|高倉永季|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takakura Nagasue|qq=}} elevated the family name by attaining the Rank of [[:en:Sangi (Japan)|Sangi]], establishing the Takakura family line.

The family name "Takakura" derives from their residence in the Takakura district of Kyoto<ref name="kotobank"/>. Their household responsibilities included overseeing court garments and the hereditary {{ill|Emondō|ja|衣紋道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emondō|qq=}} tradition <ref name="kotobank"/>.

During the [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]], the Takakura family possessed a stipend of 812 koku, with lands in {{ill|Yamashiro Province|ja|Yamashiro Province|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamashiro Province|qq=}}. Their main residence was located in Nikaimachi, and their [[:en:Bodaiji|Bodaiji]] was the Jōgen-in temple at Kurodani {{SFn|Ota Ryo|1934|p=3274}}.

=== Bakumatsu Period and Meiji Restoration ===

In the [[:en:Bakumatsu|Bakumatsu]] period, the head of the family, {{ill|Takakura Nagayoshi|ja|高倉永祜|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takakura Nagayoshi|qq=}}, played a significant role in the [[:en:Boshin War|Boshin War]], serving as a general in various campaigns. However, he died in 1868 in Echigo Province during the war<ref>{{Cite Kotobank|word=高倉永祜|encyclopedia=デジタル版 日本人名大辞典+Plus|accessdate=2022-11-16}}</ref>.

In 1869, under the new [[:en:Kazoku|Kazoku]] system, the Takakura family was ennobled as part of the [[:en:Kazoku|Kazoku]] hierarchy. In 1884, {{ill|Takakura Naganori|ja|高倉永則|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takakura Naganori|qq=}}, a former military officer, was granted the title of [[:en:Viscount|Viscount]] {{sfn|Odabe Yuji|2006|p=332}}.

== Notable Members ==
